Russia Stocks Drop 1st Day in 7 as Oil Falls, China Lifts Rates

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-07-06T15:32:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/russian-stocks-drop-1st-day-in-seven-on-oil-portugal-downgrade.html
Russian stocks closed lower for the
first time in seven days as oil fell and after  China  raised
interest rates.  The Micex Index of 30 stocks slid 0.3 percent to 1,705.41
by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, reversing an earlier gain of
as much as 0.4 percent and snapping a six-day winning streak.
OAO Lukoil,  Russia ’s second-biggest oil producer, dropped 0.8
percent while OAO Gazprom, the natural gas export monopoly, lost
0.9 percent. VTB Group, the country’s second-largest lender,
declined 2.5 percent. The-dollar denominated RTS Index fell 0.7
percent to 1,939.01.  Crude oil erased earlier gains of as much as 0.9 percent
and retreated as much as 1 percent to $95.90 a barrel in  New
York . The People’s Bank of China said benchmark deposit and
lending rates will rise 25 basis points, or 0.25 percentage
point, tomorrow.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  